-- AIRSHOW-Leasing company CIT orders 10 Boeing 787-9 planes
-- By Mark Potter
-- Tue Jul 15, 2014 08:15AM EDT
-- None



FARNBOROUGH, England, July 15 (Reuters) - U.S. leasing company CIT <CIT.N> said on Tuesday at the Farnborough Airshow that it had ordered 10 of Boeing's <BA.N> 787-9 Dreamliner planes.

The deal is worth about $2.5 billion at list prices.